<title>USA: Think New Ideas Inc Q3 loss widens.</title>
<headline>Think New Ideas Inc Q3 loss widens.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three Months Ended   Nine Months Ended</p>
<p>			 3/31/97     3/31/96     3/31/97    3/31/96</p>
<p> Revenues	  $4,211,334 $1,951,809 $12,254,066 $6,637,403</p>
<p>Operating Income</p>
<p>	  (Loss) (1,222,613)     27,511  (2,065,047)  (148,572)</p>
<p>Net Income (Loss)</p>
<p>		    (1,199,521)   (24,529) (2,178,380)  (389,296)</p>
<p> Loss per share     ( 0.21)    ( 0.01)     ( 0.51)    ( 0.16)</p>
<p>Weighted average shares</p>
<p>  outstanding     5,591,667  2,449,592   4,265,463  2,449,592</p>
<p>NOTE: The company said it acquired six subsidiaries, including On Ramp Inc in June 1996.</p>
<p>The company said Q3 and nine-month results for 1997 include a charge of $225,000 related to its acquisition of On Ramp.</p>
<p>The company said On Ramp was accounted for using the purchase method of accounting and results are included as of July 1996.</p>
<p>The company said the other acquisitions were accounted for using the pooling-of-interests method and results are included as of July 1993 or since the company's inception.</p>
